@startuml class_diagram

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam classFontStyle Bold

package "src" {
    class Calculator {
        +add(a, b) : float|int
        +subtract(a, b) : float|int
        +multiply(a, b) : float|int
        +divide(a, b) : float|int
        +factorial(n: int) : int
        +square(x) : float
        +cube(x) : float
        +square_root(x) : float
        +cube_root(x) : float
        +power(base, exp) : float
        +log(x) : float
        +ln(x) : float
    }

    class CalculatorSession {
        -{field} _calc : Calculator
        -{field} _history : list[str]
        +BINARY_OPS : frozenset[str]  <<module constant>>
        +UNARY_OPS : frozenset[str]   <<module constant>>
        +ALL_OPS : frozenset[str]     <<module constant>>
        +__init__() : None
        +execute(name: str, *args) : float|int
        +{static} format_entry(name, args, result) : str
        +history() : list[str]
        +save(path: str) : None
    }

    class "__main__" as Main <<module>> {
        +OPERATIONS : dict[str, tuple[str, int]]
        +MAX_ATTEMPTS : int
        +HISTORY_FILE : str
        +display_menu() : None
        +get_number(prompt, require_int=False) : int|float
        +get_number_with_retry(prompt, require_int=False) : int|float
        +format_history_entry(name, args, result) : str
        +save_history(history, path=None) : None
        +main() : None
        -{static} _SessionExpired <<exception>>
    }

    class "error_logger" as ErrLog <<module>> {
        +ERROR_LOG_FILE : str
        +log_error(source: str, message: str) : None
    }

    class "__init__" as Init <<module>> {
        __all__ : list
    }
}

class "main" as CLI <<module>> {
    +_parse_operand(value: str, require_int=False) : int|float
    +main(argv: list[str] | None) : int
}

package "tests" {
    class "test_calculator" as TestCalc <<module>> {
        +calc() : Calculator  <<fixture>>
        ' 76 tests covering all 12 operations
        +test_add_*()
        +test_subtract_*()
        +test_multiply_*()
        +test_divide_*()
        +test_factorial_*()
        +test_square_*()
        +test_cube_*()
        +test_square_root_*()
        +test_cube_root_*()
        +test_power_*()
        +test_log_*()
        +test_ln_*()
    }

    class "test_session" as TestSession <<module>> {
        +session() : CalculatorSession  <<fixture>>
        ' 37 tests covering CalculatorSession
        +test_op_sets_*()
        +test_format_entry_*()
        +test_execute_*()
        +test_history_*()
        +test_save_*()
    }

    class "test_main" as TestMain <<module>> {
        +run_main_with_inputs(inputs) : list[str]  <<helper>>
        ' 56 tests covering interactive CLI
        +test_operations_map_*()
        +test_get_number_*()
        +test_quit_*()
        +test_all_12_ops_end_to_end_*()
        +test_error_paths_*()
        +test_unknown_key()
        +test_multi_session_*()
        +test_format_history_entry_*()
        +test_save_history_*()
        +test_history_display_*()
        +test_history_file_written_*()
    }

    class "test_cli" as TestCLI <<module>> {
        +run_cli(args) : tuple[int, str, str]  <<helper>>
        ' 34 tests covering bash CLI
        +test_no_args()
        +test_unknown_op()
        +test_arg_count_binary_*()
        +test_arg_count_unary_*()
        +test_all_12_ops_*()
        +test_error_paths_*()
        +test_non_numeric_operand()
    }

    class "test_error_logger" as TestErrLog <<module>> {
        ' 7 tests covering error_logger
        +test_file_created()
        +test_source_and_message()
        +test_timestamp_format()
        +test_append_behavior()
        +test_one_entry_per_line()
    }

    class "conftest" as Conftest <<module>> {
        +isolate_error_log() <<autouse fixture>>
    }
}

CalculatorSession --> Calculator : holds & delegates
Main --> CalculatorSession : instantiates & delegates
Main --> ErrLog : calls log_error
CLI --> CalculatorSession : instantiates & delegates
CLI --> ErrLog : calls log_error
Init ..> Calculator : re-exports
Init ..> CalculatorSession : re-exports
TestCalc --> Calculator : tests via fixture
TestSession --> CalculatorSession : tests via fixture
TestMain --> Main : tests via mocked stdin/stdout
TestCLI --> CLI : tests via capsys
TestErrLog --> ErrLog : tests via fixture
Conftest ..> ErrLog : patches ERROR_LOG_FILE

note right of Calculator
  Division: delegates to Python "/" operator.
  ZeroDivisionError raised by runtime when b == 0.
  factorial: iterative; rejects bool/float/non-int
  (TypeError) and negatives (ValueError).
  square_root: raises ValueError for x < 0.
  cube_root: handles negatives via -(abs(x)^(1/3)).
  log: base-10 via math.log10; raises ValueError for x <= 0.
  ln: natural log via math.log; raises ValueError for x <= 0.
  power: returns base ** exp (no domain restriction).
  Imports: math
end note

note left of Main
  OPERATIONS: maps "1"–"12" to (name, arity) pairs.
  Arity 1: factorial, square, cube, square_root,
            cube_root, log, ln.
  Arity 2: add, subtract, multiply, divide, power.
  MAX_ATTEMPTS=5: max failed input attempts before
  session terminates.
  HISTORY_FILE="history.txt": path for session history.
  get_number: parses as int first, then float;
  require_int=True forces strict integer (factorial).
  get_number_with_retry: wraps get_number; prints
  remaining-attempts message on each failure; raises
  _SessionExpired after MAX_ATTEMPTS failures.
  format_history_entry: delegates to CalculatorSession.format_entry;
  kept for backward-compatible test imports.
  save_history: overwrites HISTORY_FILE with history list;
  called on all exit paths (quit, expiry, max-attempts).
  main: creates CalculatorSession; 'h' displays history;
  computation dispatched via session.execute();
  catches ValueError/TypeError/ZeroDivisionError per
  iteration; tracks invalid op selections
  (terminate after MAX_ATTEMPTS); catches _SessionExpired.
end note

note right of CalculatorSession
  BINARY_OPS: {add, subtract, multiply, divide, power}.
  UNARY_OPS: {factorial, square, cube, square_root,
              cube_root, log, ln}.
  ALL_OPS: BINARY_OPS | UNARY_OPS (12 operations total).
  Both CLIs import BINARY_OPS/ALL_OPS from here —
  single source of truth for operation arity metadata.
  execute(): dispatches via getattr(_calc, name)(*args);
  failed calls (any exception) do NOT append to history.
  format_entry(): static; "name(arg1, arg2) = result".
  history(): returns a defensive copy.
  save(): writes history to file (overwrites).
end note

note right of CLI
  Non-interactive bash CLI: one invocation, one result.
  Exit code 0 on success, 1 on any error.
  Imports BINARY_OPS, ALL_OPS from src.session
  (no local copies — single source of truth).
  _parse_operand: int first, then float;
  require_int=True for factorial.
  Errors go to stderr; result goes to stdout.
end note

@enduml
